INSERT INTO `posts` (`id`, `title`, `content`, `about_blog`, `url`, `created_at`, `category_id`) VALUES
(1, 'Jain World ', '<p>Little words of kindness, Little deeds of love, Help to make this earth, Like the heaven above. - Lord Mahavira&quot;</p>\r\n', 'Little words of kindness, Little deeds of love, Help to make this earth, Like the heaven above. ', 'jain-world', '2022-06-01 11:03:17', 5),
(2, 'Promotion  ', '<div class=\"container\">\r\n    <div class=\"row\">\r\n\r\n    <div class=\"col-md-12 mt-3\">\r\n            <b>24 Reasons to go vegetarian</b>\r\n    </div>\r\n\r\n    <div class=\"col-md-4 mt-3\"><img alt=\"animal-cruelty\" src=\"https://karunaveg.com/uploaded_images/PRO%201.jpeg\" style=\"width: 100%; height: 180px;\" /></div>\r\n    <div class=\"col-md-8 mt-3\">\r\n        <ul>\r\n            <li>\r\n                <p> 1. Every year in UK we feed livestock enough food to feed 25,00,00,000 people while 3,00,00,000 people in world die out of starvation.\r\n                    <br>2. 20 vegetarians can live in land required by one meat eater.\r\n                    <br>3. Intensification of animal farming forced over 10,00,000 people to leave their traditional land, these people land into cities succumb to dietary deficiency, disease, pesticides & other diseases.\r\n                    <br>4. UK imports over $4,60,00,000 worth of grain to feed their livestock.\r\n                    <br>5. If we continue to clear American forests at same rate to raise cattle, there would be none left after 50 years.\r\n                    <br>6. 1 acre can yield 165 lbs. Of beef or 20,000 lbs. Of potatoes.\r\n                    <br>7. Pressure on land due to meat farming leads to soil erosion about 6 billion tons in USA only.\r\n                    <br>8. Animal farming leads to global warming which is reason behind loss of land as there is rise in sea level.</p>\r\n            </li>\r\n        </ul>\r\n    </div>\r\n\r\n    <div class=\"col-md-8 mt-3\">\r\n        <ul>\r\n            <li>\r\n                <p> 9. Rain forests are lungs of earth and with their destruction for cattle farming we are reducing capacity to replenish the oxygen supply.\r\n                    <br>10. Fertilizers used to grow crop for animal fodder releases nitrogen accountable for 6% of greenhouse effects.\r\n                    <br>11. Fertilizers and weed killer sprayed on crop are mixed with air and enter our lungs causing harm to our body.\r\n                    <br>12. 25 gallon of water produce 1 lbs. Of wheat whereas 2500 gallon of water produce 1 lbs. Of meat.\r\n                    <br>13. Blood waste from slaughterhouse ends up in rivers.\r\n                    <br>14. 1 lbs. Of beef take 1 gallon of petrol to produce.\r\n                    <br>15. Eating huge quantities of animal flesh, eggs, meats and dairy products is a luxury that majority can\'t afford.\r\n                    <br>16. Nets thrown by fisherman kills ten times many other creatures than expected number of fish they want to get.\r\n                    <br>17. Fishes that get caught in nets die a slow death full of pain and agony.\r\n                    <br>18. Many hens and other poultry animals are given over diet with chemicals for weight gains leading to fractured bones and virus getting transferred into human when we eat them.\r\n                    <br>19. Broiler sheds are lit 23 hours a day to boost artificial growth.\r\n                    <br>20. 95% poultry suffer injury and broken bones before getting killed.\r\n                    <br>21. Calf leather is obtained by killing living beings that are just 2 weeks old.\r\n                    <br>22. Fish contains metals and other pollutant that reaches ocean from farms and enter into our body.\r\n                    <br>23. Vegetarians have lower chances of developing gall and kidney stones.\r\n                    <br>24. The cling film used to wrap meat contains chemicals related to falling sperm count in men.</p>\r\n            </li>\r\n        </ul>\r\n    </div>\r\n    <div class=\"col-md-4 mt-3\"><img alt=\"animal-cruelty\" src=\"https://karunaveg.com/uploaded_images/PRO%206.jpeg\" style=\"width: 100%; height: 340px;\" /></div>\r\n\r\n\r\n    <div class=\"col-md-12 mt-3\">\r\n        <b>How to win argument against meat eater</b>\r\n    </div>\r\n\r\n    <div class=\"col-md-6 mt-3\"><img alt=\"animal-cruelty\" src=\"https://karunaveg.com/uploaded_images/PRO%205.jpeg\" style=\"width: 100%; height: 180px;\" /></div>\r\n    <div class=\"col-md-6 mt-3\">\r\n        <b>The Hunger factor:</b>\r\n\r\n    <ul>\r\n        <li>\r\n            <p>Number of people who die due to malnutrition worldwide is 20 million.\r\n                Ratio of corn consumption in us by humans and livestock is 1:4.\r\n                Percentage of protein wasted by cycling grain through livestock is 90%.\r\n                Percentage of land devoted to meat production worldwide is 56%.</p>\r\n        </li>\r\n    </ul>\r\n    </div>\r\n\r\n    \r\n\r\n    <div class=\"col-md-6 mt-3\">\r\n        <b>Environment argument</b>\r\n\r\n    <ul>\r\n        <li>\r\n            <p>Cause of global warming: greenhouse effect<br>\r\n                Cause of greenhouse effect: carbon dioxide and methane released in air.<nr>\r\n                Percentage us topsoil lost due to livestock raising: 85 <br>\r\n                Acre of land consumed to cop up with land required for meat centered diet: 260 million.</p>\r\n        </li>\r\n    </ul>\r\n    </div>\r\n    <div class=\"col-md-6 mt-3\"><img alt=\"animal-cruelty\" src=\"https://karunaveg.com/uploaded_images/PRO%203.jpeg\" style=\"width: 100%; height: 180px;\" /></div>\r\n\r\n\r\n    <div class=\"col-md-6 mt-3\"><img alt=\"animal-cruelty\" src=\"https://karunaveg.com/uploaded_images/PRO%202.jpeg\" style=\"width: 100%; height: 180px;\" /></div>\r\n    <div class=\"col-md-6 mt-3\">\r\n        <b> Health argument</b>\r\n\r\n    <ul>\r\n        <li>\r\n            <p>Chances of cancer for women who eat egg daily than compared to once a week: 2.8 times.<br>\r\n                Increased risk of breast cancer for women who eat meat daily than those who consume once a week: 3.8 times. \r\n                <br>Increased risk of prostate cancer for man who eat meat, cheese, egg daily vs those who eat once a week or occasionally: 3.6 times.</p>\r\n        </li>\r\n    </ul>\r\n    </div>\r\n\r\n    \r\n\r\n    <div class=\"col-md-6 mt-3\">\r\n        <b>Ethical Argument:</b>\r\n\r\n    <ul>\r\n        <li>\r\n            <p>Number of animals killed per hour for meat: 6,60,000\r\n                Occupation with highest rate of on-job injury: slaughter houses</p>\r\n        </li>\r\n    </ul>\r\n    </div>\r\n    <div class=\"col-md-6 mt-3\"><img alt=\"animal-cruelty\" src=\"https://karunaveg.com/uploaded_images/PRO%204.jpeg\" style=\"width: 100%; height: 180px;\" /></div>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n    <div class=\"col-md-6 mt-3\"><img alt=\"animal-cruelty\" src=\"https://karunaveg.com/uploaded_images/PRO9.jpeg\" style=\"width: 100%; height: 180px;\" /></div>\r\n\r\n    <div class=\"col-md-6 mt-3\">\r\n        <b> Natural resource argument:</b>\r\n\r\n    <ul>\r\n        <li>\r\n            <p>Gallon of water needed to produce wheat: 25\r\n                Gallon of water needed to produce beef in california: 5,000\r\n                Percentage of pesticides fed to cattle: 55\r\n                Response of european economic community to regular feeding of pesticides to farm animal: ban\r\n            </p>\r\n        </li>\r\n    </ul>\r\n    </div>\r\n\r\n    \r\n\r\n    <div class=\"col-md-12 mt-5\">\r\n        <b>Spiritual benefits of vegetarianism</b>\r\n    </div>\r\n    \r\n\r\n\r\n    <div class=\"col-md-9 mt-3\">\r\n        <b>The Mind</b>\r\n    <ul>\r\n        <li>\r\n            <p> Bondage and liberation are states of mind. The mind, as a mass of vibrating energy, is limited the constitution or condition of that energy. If the energy is heavy or inert, little can be don it to produce the state of silence and clarity needed to reflect the truth of spirit. Certain elements darken the mind and make it thick or heavy, vibrating very slowly-sometimes seemingly an all. On the other hand, some elements lighten the mind, making it fluid and subtle, vibrating very high level. It is this latter condition that is needed for attaining the state of liberation rather, the state that liberates the spirit from the illusion of bondage and suffering. It is rea mind that becomes liberated, but that liberation also affects the essentially ever-free spirit sets it free. To attain such liberation the mind must be purified and refined, vegetarian die one of the best and strongest means for its purification.</p>\r\n        </li>\r\n    </ul>\r\n    </div>\r\n    <div class=\"col-md-3 mt-3\"><img alt=\"animal-cruelty\" src=\"https://karunaveg.com/uploaded_images/PRO%207.jpeg\" style=\"width: 100%; height: 120px;\" /></div>\r\n\r\n    \r\n\r\n    <div class=\"col-md-3 mt-3\"><img alt=\"animal-cruelty\" src=\"https://karunaveg.com/uploaded_images/PRO8.jpeg\" style=\"width: 100%; height: 275px;\" /></div>\r\n\r\n    <div class=\"col-md-9 mt-3\">\r\n        <b>Diet and consciousness</b>\r\n    <ul>\r\n        <li>\r\n            <p>  Although diet is commonly considered a matter of physical health alone, since the herme principle \"as above, so below\" is a fundamental truth of the cosmos, diet is a crucial aspect emotional, intellectual, and spiritual development. For diet and consciousness are interrel and purity of diet is an effective aid to purity and clarity of consciousness.<br>\r\n                The purification of our subtler levels depends upon the purification of our physical entity makes sense when we realize that all that goes to constitute a human being is formed of various types, and the only source of energy is that which is brought into the body through sunlight, air, and food. And it is material food that provides by far the greatest amount of energy from which our multilevel complex is shaped.<br>\r\n                When we realize that any physical object has all the levels which we do, namely, the physical bio magnetic, sensory, intellectual and will bodies, we can understand the importance of and quality of food we eat. For not only does the physical substance of the food become assimilated into our physical body, so also do the subtler energies become united to our levels. This is the teaching of the chandogya upanishad: \"mind consists of food. That w the subtle part of milk moves upward when the milk is churned and becomes butter. In t manner, the subtle part of the food that is eaten moves upward and becomes mind. Thus, consists of food\".<br>\r\n                We cannot get a marble statue from clay, nor can we get wheat bread from barley meal product is still going to consist of the nature of the material started with. So it is with al bodies, gross and subtle. They will reflect the character of the food which has gone int formation.   \r\n            </p>\r\n        </li>\r\n    </ul>\r\n    </div>\r\n    \r\n    \r\n', 'Vegetarianism = respect for life, co-existence and love of nature. Non vegetarianism = hate for life', 'promotion', '2022-06-01 10:49:38', 10),
(3, 'Veg./Vegan: Worldwide ', '<div class=\"container\">\r\n    <div class=\"row\">\r\n\r\n    <div class=\"col-md-12 mt-3\">\r\n    <ul>\r\n        <li>\r\n            <p><b>What is natural human diet? Are human natural meat-eaters?</b> </p>\r\n        </li>\r\n    </ul>\r\n    </div>\r\n\r\n    <div class=\"col-md-6 mt-3\"><img alt=\"animal-cruelty\" src=\"https://karunaveg.com/uploaded_images/veg-vegan4.jpeg\" style=\"width: 100%; height: 180px;\" /></div>\r\n    <div class=\"col-md-6 mt-3\">\r\n    <ul>\r\n        <li>\r\n            <p> Let\'s take a quick test. Suppose you a going on road and you see a dead bird or animal do you feel like stopping and feeding on them or you try to move on as fast as possible? Do you ever feel like killing an animal barehand and eat them up raw whenever you are hungry? If answer to all these questions is no then for sure you are herbivores believe it or not. \r\n                <br>If you see our body structure, humans have soft fingertips with small nails and canine unit. In comparison carnivores have large canine teeth to tear flesh from body. Even if we look at jawline humans can move lower jaw sidewise, up and down this help us to grind vegetables and fruits to make them digestible. But on other hand carnivores can only move their jaw up and down to tear parts of flesh from their food. \r\n                </p>\r\n        </li>\r\n    </ul>\r\n    </div>\r\n\r\n\r\n    \r\n    <div class=\"col-md-6 mt-3\">\r\n    <ul>\r\n        \r\n        <li>\r\n            <p>Moving on to digestive system, carnivores have high acid amount in stomach to break down flesh and burn down harmful bacteria that can cause diseases. Whereas in humans there are no strong acids that can do such function. Strong acids have no role to play while digesting properly chewed food, fruits and vegetables.\r\n                If we look at our ancestors, they had meat eating habits but that was in absence of green products. Our meat-eating habits developed by scavenging and eating left overs of other carnivores. However, till now even after centuries our bodies have never adopted this eating habit as a proof, we can take diseases that arise from eating meat such as heart problems, cancer, diabetes, obesity etc\r\n            </p>\r\n        </li>\r\n    </ul>\r\n    </div>\r\n    <div class=\"col-md-6 mt-3\"><img alt=\"animal-cruelty\" src=\"https://karunaveg.com/uploaded_images/veg-vegan1.jpeg\" style=\"width: 100%; height: 180px;\" /></div>\r\n    \r\n\r\n    <div class=\"col-md-12 mt-3\">\r\n        <ul>\r\n            <li>\r\n                <p><b>Reasons why popularity of vegan diet is increasing</b> </p>\r\n            </li>\r\n        </ul>\r\n        </div>\r\n    \r\n\r\n    <div class=\"col-md-3 mt-3\"><img alt=\"animal-cruelty\" src=\"https://karunaveg.com/uploaded_images/veg-vegan2.jpeg\" style=\"width: 100%; height: 120px;\" /></div>\r\n\r\n    <div class=\"col-md-9 mt-3\">\r\n    <ul>\r\n        <li>\r\n        <p><b> 1. Health concerns:  :</b> People are now becoming more health conscious realising what damage excessive protein do to their body especially the red meat, pork and beef. They are afraid of heart attacks strokes and cancer. \r\n        </p>\r\n        </li>\r\n    </ul>\r\n    </div>\r\n    \r\n    \r\n\r\n    <div class=\"col-md-3 mt-3\"><img alt=\"animal-cruelty\" src=\"https://karunaveg.com/uploaded_images/veg-vegan3.jpeg\" style=\"width: 100%; height: 120px;\" /></div>\r\n\r\n    <div class=\"col-md-9 mt-3\">\r\n    <ul>\r\n        <li>\r\n        <p><b> 2. Health benefits of plant-based diet:  </b> There are a lot of evidence going in favour of plant-based diets. They give a lot of contribution to growth of mind and body. Some researchers suggest that herbivores have chances to have a longer life cycle than carnivores or omnivores. \r\n        </p>\r\n        </li>\r\n    </ul>\r\n    </div>\r\n    \r\n    \r\n\r\n    <div class=\"col-md-3 mt-3\"><img alt=\"animal-cruelty\" src=\"https://karunaveg.com/uploaded_images/veg-vegan11.jpeg\" style=\"width: 100%; height: 120px;\" /></div>\r\n\r\n    <div class=\"col-md-9 mt-3\">\r\n    <ul>\r\n        <li>\r\n        <p><b> 3. Animal welfare/Moral values:   </b>For many people reason to discontinue their meat diet is animal cruelty. They believe that treatment through which an animal goes through, brutality and living conditions they face are unbearable.  Even animals have right to life and freedom. \r\n \r\n        </p>\r\n        </li>\r\n    </ul>\r\n    </div>\r\n    \r\n    \r\n\r\n    <div class=\"col-md-3 mt-3\"><img alt=\"animal-cruelty\" src=\"https://karunaveg.com/uploaded_images/veg-vegan5.jpeg\" style=\"width: 100%; height: 120px;\" /></div>\r\n\r\n    <div class=\"col-md-9 mt-3\">\r\n    <ul>\r\n        <li>\r\n        <p><b> 4. Environment activism: </b>People who eat plant diet are more concerned about environment and nature. The land and water resources that are wasted while animal farming can be used for other development purposes. \r\n \r\n        </p>\r\n        </li>\r\n    </ul>\r\n    </div>\r\n    \r\n\r\n    <div class=\"col-md-3 mt-3\"><img alt=\"animal-cruelty\" src=\"https://karunaveg.com/uploaded_images/veg-vegan6.jpeg\" style=\"width: 100%; height: 120px;\" /></div>\r\n\r\n    <div class=\"col-md-9 mt-3\">\r\n    <ul>\r\n        <li>\r\n        <p><b> 5. Believes and preference:  </b> Some people are considering plant-based diet to be sufficient for providing energy to human to perform daily tasks and survive. While this is a fact that you can fulfil your nutrient requirement from plant diet. On the other hand, some people simply don\'t like animal products and hence go for complete vegan diet.  \r\n        </p>\r\n        </li>\r\n    </ul>\r\n    </div>\r\n    \r\n    \r\n    <div class=\"col-md-12 mt-3\">\r\n        <ul>\r\n            <li>\r\n                <p><b>Celebrity going vegan</b> </p>\r\n            </li>\r\n            <li>\r\n                <p>Many celebrities are going vegan either for their brand value or for social cause.  Plant based diet have become more famous for health and fitness industry over a couple of years. Studies show that vegan diet is healthy, sustainable and convincing for people and earth for proper working and wellness.  </p>\r\n            </li>\r\n        </ul>\r\n    </div>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n    <div class=\"col-md-6 mt-3\"><img alt=\"animal-cruelty\" src=\"https://karunaveg.com/uploaded_images/veg-vegan7.jpeg\" style=\"width: 100%; height: 380px;\" /></div>\r\n    <div class=\"col-md-6 mt-3\">\r\n        <ul>\r\n            <li>\r\n                <b>Some celebrity that are going vegan are :</b>\r\n            </li>\r\n            <li>\r\n                <p><b> 1. Anushka Sharma and Virat Kohli:  </b> They moved to plant-based diet due to love for animals. They are investing in plant-based meat brand, blue tribe.\r\n \r\n            </li>\r\n            <li>\r\n                <p><b> 2. Genelia D\'Souza and Ritesh Deshmukh: </b> This celebrity couple has invested in plant-based product by launching their own brand called Imagine meat.\r\n            </li>\r\n            <li>\r\n                <p><b> 3. Alia Bhatt:  </b> She reportedly switched to plant product for love of animals and invested in brand Phool.co that developed a product known as Fleather, plant-based alternative for animal leather\r\n            </li>\r\n            <li>\r\n                <p><b> 4. Jay Z: :  </b> Rapper, producer and writer Jay Z is one of the first few celebrities to move into world of plant-based products, now he is supporting many other stars who are taking steps in this direction. He invested in Impossible Foods, an alternative for meat brand behind \"meaty\" Impossible burger.\r\n            </li>\r\n            <li>\r\n                <p><b> 5. Drake:  </b> During a live stream Drake revealed that for his health, environment and animals, he wasn\'t eating meat anymore. He further invested in plant-based business \"Daring Food\" that create plant-based chicken product.\r\n\r\n            </li>\r\n            <li>\r\n                <p><b> 6. Robert Downey Jr.:   </b> Marvels Iron Man star RDJ revealed his transition towards plant-based diet in 2020. He sent his money into Atlas Food Co. a meat alternative brand which focus on entire plant-based meat.\r\n            </li>\r\n        </ul>\r\n    </div>\r\n\r\n\r\n    \r\n    <div class=\"col-md-12 mt-3\">\r\n        <ul>\r\n            <li>\r\n                <p><b>Books recommending a vegan diet </b> </p>\r\n            </li>\r\n            <li>\r\n                <p>Some great books about vegetarianism are listed below. More books could\'ve been added but these are prominent and esteemed.\r\n                </p>\r\n            </li>\r\n        </ul>\r\n    </div>\r\n\r\n    <div class=\"col-md-6 mt-3\">\r\n        <ul>\r\n  \r\n            <li>\r\n                <p><b> 1. Elizabeth Costello by JM Coetzee:  </b> This novel revolves around some formal lectures containing a few on animal rights. The writer Coetzee compares the sheep cattle with the way people were compared at Nazi concentration camps.\r\n \r\n            </li>\r\n            <li>\r\n                <p><b> 2. Ethical Vegetarianism edited by Kerry S Walters and Lisa Portmess:  </b> : As name speaks for itself, taken from huge range of studies and analysis by avowed carnivores the theoretical arguments make this worth reading. Also, it is very beneficial for debate purpose.\r\n\r\n            </li>\r\n            <li>\r\n                <p><b> 3. Collected stories by Isaac Bashevis Singer:  </b> Singer lives close to slaughterhouse, hence swearing not to take meat. In his stories from old world Poland and mid-century New York there\'s at least one character who unassumingly follows suit. The environment of slaughterhouse is entirely brutal, the routine of butcher is totally inhuman with no space for sensitivity and sanity.\r\n\r\n            </li>\r\n            <li>\r\n                <p><b> 4. Charlotte\'s web:  </b>As spider makes its web to catch flies and eat them, the same way Charlotte use her web to make the word \"Some Pig\". She\'s on humanitarian mission to save some pigs from being slaughtered. \r\n            </li>\r\n            <li>\r\n                <p><b> 5. Animals: A novel by Don LePan: </b> In this sarcastic scene set in an imminent future, we people have eaten every one of the creatures, yet have not lost our preference for meat. Barbarianism is the sensible arrangement. Assuming we ate creatures since we were better than them, their rationale goes, why not eat the genuinely and slow-witted? Furthermore, why not keep a hard of hearing kid as a pet?\r\n\r\n            </li>\r\n            <li>\r\n                <p><b> 6. The jungle by Upton Sinclair:   </b> The novel talks about immigrant working in slaughterhouse of Chicago. It covers the heinous act and exploitation of animals and employees at slaughterhouses. The process that caused imposing of American Clean Food and Drug act. The novel brought a rise in veganism\r\n            </li>\r\n        </ul>\r\n    </div>\r\n    <div class=\"col-md-6 mt-3\"><img alt=\"animal-cruelty\" src=\"https://karunaveg.com/uploaded_images/veg-vegan8.jpeg\" style=\"width: 100%; height: 400px;\" /></div>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n    <div class=\"col-md-6 mt-3\"><img alt=\"animal-cruelty\" src=\"https://karunaveg.com/uploaded_images/veg-vegan9.jpeg\" style=\"width: 100%; height: 380px;\" /></div>\r\n\r\n    <div class=\"col-md-6 mt-3\">\r\n    <ul>\r\n        <li>\r\n            <p><b> Mock meat </b> </p>\r\n        </li>\r\n        <li>\r\n        <p> Mock meat or meat basic is a meat substitute that takes after the surface and consistency of meat and meat things and consequently is used in game plans like the ones using meat things. It is every now and again created utilizing veggie lover trimmings and non-dairy things. Soya, gluten, and pea protein are a few regularly used trimmings.\r\n            There is approx. 17 gm of protein in 100 gm of misleading meat. Presumably the most ordinarily available fake meat varieties are:\r\n            </p>\r\n        </li>\r\n        <ul>\r\n            <li>\r\n                <p>Soy-based. </p>\r\n            </li>\r\n            <li>\r\n                <p>- Grain-based poultry. </p>\r\n            </li>\r\n            <li>\r\n                <p>- Quinoa flour-based counterfeit meats have all of the vital 9 amino acids and are a phenomenal choice. </p>\r\n            </li>\r\n            <li>\r\n                <p>- Wheat flour-based vegan meat is used in biryanis and burgers. </p>\r\n            </li>\r\n            <li>\r\n                <p>- Seitan is plant-based mock meat that is high in protein </p>\r\n            </li>\r\n        </ul>\r\n    </ul>\r\n    </div>\r\n\r\n\r\n    \r\n    \r\n    <div class=\"col-md-9 mt-3\">\r\n    <ul>\r\n        <li>\r\n            <p>Things you should know:  </p>\r\n        </li>\r\n        <li>\r\n        <p>Sodium is regularly utilized in handled veg meat for adding flavour and expanding its time frame of realistic usability. High measures of sodium present in some counterfeit meat assortments can put weight on your renal framework. Henceforth, try to take a look at the fixings.\r\n            Mock meat can be a favoured decision over carb-weight veggie lover food. Plant-based proteins have various medical advantages. They help in adjusting the glucose levels and are useful for the gut. They likewise bring down the danger of cardiovascular illnesses as they are generally liberated from cholesterol.\r\n            </p>\r\n        </li>\r\n    </ul>\r\n    </div>\r\n    <div class=\"col-md-3 mt-3\"><img alt=\"animal-cruelty\" src=\"https://karunaveg.com/uploaded_images/veg-vegan10.jpeg\" style=\"width: 100%; height: 140px;\" /></div>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n', 'Vegetarianism is the practice of abstaining from the consumption of meat.', 'veg-vegan-worldwide', '2022-06-01 11:18:03', 12),
(4, 'Nutrition', '<div class=\"container\">\r\n    <div class=\"row\">\r\n    \r\n    \r\n    \r\n    <div class=\"col-md-12 mt-3\">\r\n    <ul>\r\n        <li><h5><b>Nutrition</b></h5></li>\r\n\r\n    </ul>\r\n    </div>\r\n    \r\n    <div class=\"col-md-6 mt-3\"><img alt=\"animal-cruelty\" src=\"https://karunaveg.com/uploaded_images/nutrition4.jpeg\" style=\"width: 100%; height: 180px;\" /></div>\r\n\r\n    <div class=\"col-md-6 mt-3\">\r\n    <ul>\r\n\r\n        <li>\r\n        <p>Our bodies are worked and controlled mainly by what we eat and drink. Food is the major source of all of the energy required. Why do people need to eat? Is it only to remove hunger? That\'s not the main concern. We really need energy constantly, when we run, work or even sing and in any event when we rest. We make all the energy we want by eating. The designs parts that make up the human body, like muscles, organs, and bones, are additionally made out of the supplements contained in food, implying that when used. That\'s why eating and taking in the nutrients that give energy to the parts of our body designs important for supporting human existence.\r\n            Nutrients are the substances found in food which drive natural movement, and are important for the human body. They are classified as proteins, fats, carbs (sugars, dietary fibre), nutrients, and minerals, and carry out the accompanying imperative roles.</p>\r\n        </li>\r\n    </ul>\r\n    </div>\r\n    \r\n    \r\n\r\n    <div class=\"col-md-12 mt-3\">\r\n    <ul>\r\n        <li><h5><b>Herbivores carnivores and omnivores</b></h5></li>\r\n    </ul>\r\n    </div>\r\n\r\n    <div class=\"col-md-6 mt-3\">\r\n    <ul>\r\n\r\n        <li>\r\n        <p>There are three categories of living beings on basis of eating habits. Those who take only plant diet are herbivores, those who eat completely animal/meat diet are carnivores and those who eat both plant and animal diet are omnivores. The working of ecosystem depends on existence of all of these categories. \r\n            With an eating routine contained just plants, herbivores can be shockingly huge creatures. Instances of huge herbivores incorporate cows, elephant and bison. These creatures eat grass, tree covering, oceanic vegetation, and shrubby development. Herbivores can likewise be medium-sized creatures, for example, sheep and goats, which eat shrubby vegetation and grasses. Little herbivores incorporate bunnies, chipmunks, squirrels, and mice. These creatures eat grass, bushes, seeds, and nuts. An environment should give plentiful plants to support herbivores, and a large number of them spend most of their lives eating to remain alive. Assuming plant accessibility declines, herbivores might not have enough to eat. This could cause a decrease in herbivore numbers, which would likewise influence carnivores. Omnivores have much advantage in ecosystem due to their diversified diet. They can go on both meat and plant depending on availability. Omnivores eat herbivores but sometime they canâ€™t eat grass and plants directly due to digestive limitations. \r\n            </li>\r\n    </ul>\r\n    </div>\r\n    \r\n    <div class=\"col-md-6 mt-3\"><img alt=\"animal-cruelty\" src=\"https://karunaveg.com/uploaded_images/nutrition1.jpeg\" style=\"width: 100%; height: 180px;\" /></div>\r\n\r\n\r\n    <div class=\"col-md-12 mt-3\">\r\n        <ul>\r\n            <li><h5><b>Food components</b></h5></li><br>\r\n            <li><p>Food components have six nutrition that are proteins, fats, carbohydrates, sugar and sodium along with this some nutrients that you may get are fibre and calcium. Different food products have different quantities of nutrients. To make a healthier choice you need to take a product with low fats, low sodium, low sugar and high fibre. Let\'s study food components in detail.</p></li>\r\n            \r\n            <ul style=\"padding-left: 20px;\">\r\n                <li><p><b>1. Fat sugar & salt: </b>Fat, sugar or salt component can be listed by different name depending on food product o ingredient. These components might seem hidden in food products or ingredient list, but whenever there is high fat, salt or sugar it generally means that food is less healthy.\r\n                </li>\r\n                <li><p><b>2. Energy:</b> Fats, proteins and carbohydrates all provide you energy in kilojoules unit. In order to perform daily tasks or working of body you need to get sufficient amount of energy in body. When you compare different kind of food products you watch for products that have low fats, high carbohydrates and high protein. Products with these qualities are better to consume and healthier.\r\n                </p></li>\r\n                <li><p><b>3. Cholesterol:</b> Sometime a product is cholesterol free but that doesn\'t mean it don\'t contain fats. Cholesterol leads to fat gaining and might cause problems like obesity and heart problems.\r\n                </p></li>\r\n                <li><p><b>4. Additives: </b> Some juices, ice creams and drinks may contain added flavours and colours to make item tastier and attractive. These things make food tastier and we might enjoy them but consuming them regularly and in high quantity creates health issues. </p></li>\r\n                <li><p><b>5. Reduced fat or sugar free: </b> Some product claim to have low sucrose than other competitors but that doesn\'t mean that sugar content in that product is low and you can consume it freely in high quantity.\r\n                </p></li>\r\n                <li><p><b>6. Oven baked: </b>These are the product that are sprayed or coated with some fat containing items like butter or oil before baking. This process usually increases fat content in product which makes food unhealthy.</p></li>\r\n\r\n            </ul>\r\n        </ul>\r\n    </div>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n    <div class=\"col-md-12 mt-3\">\r\n    <ul>\r\n        <li><h5><b>Too much protein intake </b></h5></li><br>\r\n\r\n        <li>\r\n            <p>Sometime we take too much protein or supplement to gain muscles or make body fitter an in this process we ignore other nutrients required in body. In early stages or for some time this might seem a good deal but for longer run this could prove very dangerous. Dietitians and doctors don\'t suggest to take protein more than daily requirement. There are several issues that arise due to excessive protein intake such as</p>\r\n        </li>\r\n        <ul style=\"padding-left: 20px;\">\r\n            <li><p> <b>1.  Bad breath: </b>Controlling your nutrition intake and increasing amount of protein only can lead to shortage of carbs in your body. This will force body to take energy from other sources and hence some chemicals are produced that creates unpleasant fumes. \r\n            </p></li>\r\n            <li><p> <b>2.  Constipation: </b>High protein intake and low fibre intake is also not good. The nutrients go into body undigested to keep your digestive system clean and healthy for easy movements. If you are taking too much protein and dairy products then it might lead to digestive issues and even diarrhoea.</p></li>\r\n            <li><p> <b>3.  Brain fogging: </b>: High amount of protein and lower amount of carbs leads to low supply of sugar into your brain. This can lead to shrinking of brain due to which you might feel hazy or foggy. For your brain to work properly, carb is main source of energy and deficiency of carbs might lead to you brain functioning affecting your concentration and mood.</p>\r\n            </li>\r\n            <li><p> <b>4.  Hydration level: </b>Protein intake at higher amount can actually decrease your Hydration level in body. If there is excess of protein in your body, your kidney will remove extra protein and nitrogen in form of water waste i.e., eventually you\'ll urinate too much. In long runs you will need more amount of water and also affecting your kidney.</p></li>\r\n            <li><p> <b>5.  Weight gains:   </b>When you go for high protein intake you might gain some extra weight. But this process will be short term only. The excess of protein is generally stored in your body with amino acids excretion. Hence temporary wait gain. </p></li>\r\n        </ul>    \r\n    </ul>\r\n    </div>\r\n    \r\n    \r\n    <div class=\"col-md-12 mt-3\">\r\n        <ul>\r\n            <li><h5><b>Advantages of vegan diet over meat diet </b></h5></li>\r\n    \r\n        </ul>\r\n        </div>\r\n           \r\n        <div class=\"col-md-6 mt-3\">\r\n        <ul>\r\n    \r\n            <li>\r\n            <p>Many health issues like heart problem, various types of cancer, obesity, high cholesterol or diabetes can be cured or prevented by vegan diet if taken carefully. Junk food, refined grains and sweets are trouble makers for any person irrespective of their diet if its vegan diet or meat diet. To stay healthy all you need is plenty of nutrients like vitamins, essential fatty acids, iron, protein and carbohydrates.   </p></li>\r\n        </ul>\r\n        </div>        \r\n\r\n    <div class=\"col-md-6 mt-3\"><img alt=\"animal-cruelty\" src=\"https://karunaveg.com/uploaded_images/nutrition2.jpeg\" style=\"width: 100%; height: 180px;\" /></div>\r\n    <!-- --------------------------------------------------------------- -->\r\n    \r\n   \r\n    </div>\r\n    </div>\r\n    ', '\"Every time you eat is an opportunity to nourish your body\"', 'Nutrition', '2022-07-08 11:01:40', 1),
(5, 'Meat vs Disease ', '<div class=\"container\">\r\n    <div class=\"row\">\r\n    <div class=\"col-md-12 mt-3\">\r\n    <ul>\r\n        <li>\r\n        <p>Eating meat is harming environment that point is straight and clear but does it harm human health as well? Is eating meat good for humans or it have equally bad effects on human body? So, as we talk about flesh consumption it has worst charge on human body it can create complexities in digestive system, it can cause problems like sugar and Blood Pressure affecting your daily life or it can give you a life-threatening disease as well. Studies conducted by modern scientists worldwide clearly shows that a person consuming meat is more likely to catch diseases like cancer, heart problems, blood pressure and obesity as compared to one who don&rsquo;t.</p>\r\n        </li>\r\n    </ul>\r\n    </div>\r\n    \r\n    <div class=\"col-md-6 mt-3\"><img alt=\"meat-vs-disease\" src=\"https://karunaveg.com/uploaded_images/Meat%20vs%20Disease2.jpeg\" style=\"width: 100%; height: 180px;\" /></div>\r\n    \r\n    <div class=\"col-md-6 mt-3\">\r\n    <ul>\r\n        <li>\r\n        <p><b>Cancer:</b> According to reports of World Health Organization (WHO) consumption of meat products like beef, pork, lamb, chicken, pig, bacon etc. are directly causing you cancer. The main cause of this problem is substances that are contained in animal products. Some of them are nitrates, nitrites and amines of different type. These can mainly breast cancer, prostate cancer, stomach cancer, colon cancer and lymphoma. So as an alternative why don&rsquo;t we move to plant-based diet which is full of anti-cancer materials that increase your life spam and fills you with energy and fitness. After looking at all these points its quite clear that lets go vegan and avoid cancer to a large extend.</p>\r\n        </li>\r\n    </ul>\r\n    </div>\r\n    \r\n    <br>\r\n    <div class=\"col-md-6 mt-3\">\r\n    <ul><br>\r\n        <li>\r\n        <p><b>Heart disease:</b> More than a quarter of deaths worldwide are caused by heart issues. All these animal products like meat, eggs etc. are full of cholesterol and fats that gets collected in body and gradually blocks arteries and cause heart issues. Eating meat just a couple of times in week increase risk of heart problems by a high rate. On the other side of coin, we have vegan products that are totally fat free with high content of fiber that rules out excessive fat from our body. It makes proper and regular blood supply in body helping blood cells to reach our heart decreasing chances of heart attack or strokes caused by clotting.</p>\r\n        </li>\r\n    </ul>\r\n    </div>\r\n    \r\n    <div class=\"col-md-6 mt-3\"><img alt=\"meat-vs-disease\" src=\"https://karunaveg.com/uploaded_images/Meat%20vs%20Disease.jpeg\" style=\"width: 100%; height: 180px;\" /></div>\r\n    \r\n\r\n    <!-- --------------------------------------------------------------- -->\r\n    \r\n    <div class=\"col-md-6 mt-3\"><img alt=\"meat-vs-disease\" src=\"https://karunaveg.com/uploaded_images/Meat%20vs%20Disease4.jpeg\" style=\"width: 100%; height: 200px;\" /></div>\r\n    \r\n    <div class=\"col-md-6 mt-3\">\r\n    <ul><br>\r\n        <li>\r\n            <p><b>Obesity:</b>With no surprise substance that are found in animal product and cause heart problems, fats and cholesterol also cause obesity. But at opposite end plant-based diet results ion low fat consumption and less body mass index. This regular meat consumption makes us excessively over weighted and not only for us but for our future generations as well, being a disease that moves on from one generation to other. So, its curtail that we and our children adopt a health-based diet and take a step against meal that is continuously reducing our life cycle.</p>\r\n            <p><b>Diabetes:</b> If we take up data of developed nation, one out of every 10 people above age of forty is suffering from type two diabetes. A significant cause behind this is consumption of substance known as haem iron found in meat products. Adopting a diet based on plants can reduce your chance of diabetes by 20-60 percent.</p>\r\n        </li>\r\n    </ul>\r\n    </div>\r\n    <!-- --------------------------------------------------------------- -->\r\n    \r\n    <div class=\"col-md-6 mt-3\">\r\n    <ul><br>\r\n        <li>\r\n        <p><b>Zoonotic diseases:</b> In simple words if we say these are diseases that are transfer from animals to humans. Many major diseases that are spread from viruses and cause epidemics are caused by animals, for example COVID-19, Ebola, swine flu, bird flu etc. Many slaughterhouses, poultry farms, animal farms are home for these diseases to evolve. All these unhealthy and unclean conditions in animal farms along with chemicals given to them are like a ticking bomb for human population that can explode anytime giving us another epidemic outbreak. Those animals are living in such a space that is filled with their waste and unwanted gases like methane and ammonia causing damage to their immune system hence if disease arises in one, in no time it will spread to others and finally reach to out food. As long as we keep on going on this track in no time, we can another pandemic.</p>\r\n        </li>\r\n    </ul>\r\n    </div>\r\n    <div class=\"col-md-6 mt-3\"><img alt=\"meat-vs-disease\" src=\"https://karunaveg.com/uploaded_images/man-vs-dis.jpeg\" style=\"width: 100%; height: 180px;\" /></div>\r\n\r\n    <!-- --------------------------------------------------------------- -->\r\n    \r\n    <div class=\"col-md-12 mt-3\">\r\n    <ul>\r\n        <li><b>Hunger</b>\r\n    \r\n        <p>Some people claim that meat consumption is an alternative for plant diet in order to save environment but that is totally fake. We can easily feed world&rsquo;s population even if we stop eating meat. In many prospects plant diet is much better in terms of land used, animal diet needed, water usage and chemicals injected in them. For our nutrition need we can easily grow plant-based protein in much less land used for animal grazing. Food varieties related with working on human wellbeing - including entire grains, organic products, vegetables, heartbeats, seeds, and nuts - are among those that have the most minimal natural effect. Picking a plant-based diet is great for our wellbeing, can assist with handling food neediness, safeguards the climate, and forestalls creature languishing.</p>\r\n        </li>\r\n    </ul>\r\n    </div>\r\n    \r\n    <div class=\"col-md-6 mt-3\">\r\n    <ul>\r\n        <li><b>What&rsquo;s the solution?</b>\r\n    \r\n        <p>The answer is simple go vegan. Help yourself, other human on planet, environment and more importantly animals. Choose a plant-based diet for sake of billion of animals and human beings who dies of disease caused by animal meat consumption. Hence its upon you either go for vegan diet and live longer with considerably better lifestyle, fitter, heathier and a great feeling. You eat something that cause no suffering to other.</p>\r\n        </li>\r\n    </ul>\r\n    </div>\r\n    \r\n    <div class=\"col-md-6 mt-3\"><img alt=\"meat-vs-disease\" src=\"https://karunaveg.com/uploaded_images/Meat%20vs%20Disease5.jpeg\" style=\"width: 100%; height: 180px;\" /></div>\r\n    </div>\r\n    </div>\r\n    ', 'Eating meat is harming environment that point is straight and clear but does it harm human health as well?', 'meat-vs-disease', '2022-06-11 11:18:49', 6);
INSERT INTO `posts` (`id`, `title`, `content`, `about_blog`, `url`, `created_at`, `category_id`) VALUES
(6, 'Meat vs Environment ', '<div class=\"container\">\r\n    <div class=\"row\">\r\n    <div class=\"col-md-12 mt-3\">\r\n        <p>Diet, it is something that determine some major things of our daily schedule and plays significant role in our culture and wellbeing. As we are growing, now we have a huge range of products to choose how and what we eat but still the fact is that growth requires more resources. \r\n            If we look at todayâ€™s meat industry and its impact on planet it can have a good argument whether meat is good or not for environment. We can make some argument that are there some good alternatives for meat or not.\r\n            </p>\r\n    \r\n    </div>\r\n    \r\n    <div class=\"col-md-12 mt-3\">\r\n        <b>In the History</b>\r\n        <p>There have been many researches by archeologist and anthropologists regarding structure of human teeth and cut marks on bones of herbivores just to know how long our ancestor have been eating meat. Experts suggest that we are consuming flesh around 2.7 million years ago.\r\n        It is believed that this protein rich diet played an important role in our evolution. This energy rich protein helped our brain to get much required energy to evolve and that is the reason that our ancestor search for meat instead of hunting for it. Along with brain evolvement it played an important role in shaping our digestive system. Although after cooking was invented, the meat become more digestive for us.\r\n        With human emerging around 3 lakh years ago hunting and eating meat with plant and fruits was common until introduction of agriculture around 10 thousand years ago. Which made us shift to some narrow diet like wheat, rice, corn, etc.\r\n        With time meat become a luxury and was consumed either by limited people or only on some special occasion. But now as we see, it can be found in abundance with majority of people consuming meat.\r\n        </p>\r\n    \r\n    </div>\r\n    \r\n    <div class=\"col-md-12 mt-3\">\r\n        <b>Is Meet really good?</b>\r\n        <p>Though the number of people who prefer animal product are getting increased but the question arises is that right? There is a considerable reason who prefer to go vegan and not consume any kind of meat like fish, chicken or goat. Talking about developed countries like UK there were about 1.5 lakh people in 2019 who were not consuming meat items.</p>\r\n    \r\n    </div>\r\n    \r\n    \r\n    <div class=\"col-md-12 mt-3\">\r\n    <b>There are plenty of reasons which questions that is meat really good for environment.</b><br>\r\n    </div>\r\n    \r\n    <div class=\"col-md-12 mt-3\">\r\n    <ul>\r\n        <li><p><b>1. Animal welfare:</b> Movement towards low-cost meat is taking us to intensive farming. Animal are kept in limited space with cost saving methods restricting their behavior from natural habitat. This compromises their health and welfare.</p></li>\r\n    </ul>\r\n    </div>\r\n    \r\n    \r\n    \r\n    <div class=\"col-md-6 mt-3\"><img alt=\"Meat-vs-enviornment\" src=\"https://karunaveg.com/uploaded_images/Meat%20vs%20Environment1.jpeg\" style=\"width: 100%; height: 180px;\" /></div>\r\n    <div class=\"col-md-6 mt-3\">\r\n    <ul>\r\n        <li><p><b>2. Sustainability:</b> Land required for animal farming is extremely higher in ratio, the farms and gazing lands etc. According to studies the land used for livestock production is nearly 77% yet when it comes to calory consumption it is just 17% from animals.</p></li>\r\n    </ul>\r\n    </div>\r\n    \r\n    \r\n    \r\n    <div class=\"col-md-6 mt-3\">\r\n        <ul>\r\n            <br>\r\n            <li><p><b>3. Environmental damage:</b> The grazing animals eats grass from soil which leads to soil erosion that have numerous side effects like flood, soil losing its fertility, land slide in hilly regions and even floods. Livestock production is main driver of environmental damage which include climate change and biodiversity loss. \r\n            <li><p><b>4. Deforestation:</b> Cattle farming need space. In order to get that space forests are cleared and habitats are created where grazing land are made. Generally, these forests are cleared using fire, that means more damage is added. Firstly the forests are cleared that decrease oxygen production secondly fire produced CO2 that leads to global warming and heating effect. </p></li>\r\n\r\n            </p></li>   \r\n        </ul>\r\n    </div>\r\n    <div class=\"col-md-6 mt-3\"><img alt=\"Meat-vs-enviornment\" src=\"https://karunaveg.com/uploaded_images/Meat%20vs%20Environment3.jpeg\" style=\"width: 100%; height: 200px;\" /></div>\r\n        \r\n    <br>\r\n    \r\n    <div class=\"col-md-6 mt-3\"><img alt=\"Meat-vs-enviornment\" src=\"https://karunaveg.com/uploaded_images/Meat-vs-env.jpeg\" style=\"width: 100%; height: 200px;\" /></div>\r\n\r\n    <div class=\"col-md-6 mt-3\">\r\n        <ul>\r\n            <br>\r\n            <br><li><p><b>5. Greenhouse effect:</b> Consumption of non veg is highly responsible for greenhouse effect. Cattle animal release methane while digesting food, animal produce and fertilizers that are nitrogen based (produce nitrous oxide). These gases trap heat causing temperature rise and further several serious issues.</p></li>\r\n        </ul>\r\n    </div>\r\n        \r\n    \r\n    \r\n    <div class=\"col-md-6 mt-3\"><img alt=\"Meat-vs-enviornment\" src=\"https://karunaveg.com/uploaded_images/Meat%20vs%20Environment4.jpeg\" style=\"width: 100%; height: 180px;\" /></div>\r\n    \r\n    <div class=\"col-md-6 mt-3\">\r\n    <ul>\r\n    \r\n        <li><p><b>6. Biodiversity loss: </b> It is not just that trees are destructed due to land requirement but many animal species loose their home and might face extinction or get under serious threat due to lose of natural habitat. Researchers suggest that half of worlds habitable land is used for agriculture of which nearly 77% is used for cattle grazing which means that this portion of land canâ€™t be use to give habitat to endangered animal or plant species. </p></li>\r\n    </ul>\r\n    </div>\r\n    \r\n    \r\n    <div class=\"col-md-6 mt-3\">\r\n    \r\n        <ul><br>\r\n            <li><p><b>7. Water problem: </b> Production of animal product such as beef, pork or meat takes up about four times water than any other alternative source of protein. It is very clear that these are water intensive production. Beside this the manure used for production of soyabean (animal feed) pollutes water worldwide and contaminated underground water is for sure unsafe at high rate. </p></li>\r\n            <li><p><b>8. Soil degradation:</b> Grazing land for animals leads to bare soil that gradually gets lost due to rain or high wind. Resulting in conversion of fertile land into barren fields and create either drought like situation or increasing flood risk. </p></li>\r\n\r\n        </ul>\r\n    </div>\r\n    \r\n    <div class=\"col-md-6 mt-3\"><img alt=\"Meat-vs-enviornment\" src=\"https://karunaveg.com/uploaded_images/Meat%20vs%20Environment2.jpeg\" style=\"width: 100%; height: 200px;\" /></div>\r\n    <!-- --------------------------------------------------------------- -->\r\n\r\n    <div class=\"col-md-12 mt-3\">\r\n        <b>Is eating meat bad for planet?  </b>\r\n        <p>From the above evidence we can clearly conclude that eating meat products do cause harm to nature. It ultimately ends up at your personal choice, looking at cultural, ethical and environmental factors that you want to take up animal product or alternative source of protein as your diet at risk of our earth. \r\n            It highly depends on personal choice that what a person consumes but other factors such as choice of a farmer, Government factors and local shopkeepers either they want to promote animal products or normal goods.  \r\n            </p>\r\n    \r\n    </div>\r\n    \r\n    </div>\r\n    </div>\r\n    ', 'Diet, it is something that determine some major things of our daily schedule and plays ', 'meat-vs-environment', '2022-06-13 12:44:24', 7),
(7, 'Poultry ', '<div class=\"container\">\r\n<div class=\"row\">\r\n<div class=\"col-md-12 mt-3\">\r\n<p>Chickens, animals that face cruelty at a very mass rate on this planet. The amount of suffering and death rate of chicken in farms and factory are truly shocking. Let&rsquo;s have a broad look at this to know more about chicken crisis that&rsquo;s arising all over the globe.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"col-md-6 mt-3\">\r\n<p>Every problem has its own story, its background, causes and effect. At some point of time when any kind of problem arises it looks too small and often gets ignored but then also comes a point when people get aware and look into the matter to resolve it ASAP. Let&rsquo;s take an example of recent problem that shook us COVID 19. In early stages the COVID cases were ignored and it was taken as normal viral but soon we realized that there was much bigger picture behind it and countries took quick action to control it considering it as a global emergency. The same goes on for poultry animals. The chickens that suffer daily at wide range create a problem in animal welfare. The story of mass suffering may not affect our brains but if we see a single story it will motivate people reason being our brain is built in such a way that it prioritize single story over scale.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"col-md-6 mt-3\"><img alt=\"poultry\" src=\"https://karunaveg.com/uploaded_images/poultry3.jpeg\" style=\"width: 100%; height: 180px;\" /></div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"col-md-6 mt-3\"><img alt=\"poultry\" src=\"https://karunaveg.com/uploaded_images/poultry2.jpeg\" style=\"width: 100%; height: 320px;\" /></div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"col-md-6 mt-3\">\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><b>MODERN PROBLEM</b>\r\n\r\n	<p>When it comes to chicken meet, globally we use white feathered chicken who barely balance on their feet managing their body weight. They are just 40 days old when they are brought to be slaughtered and served. Its not just that they are too young but the thing is their genetics are being disturbed and they are turned in such a way that they gain a lot of weight that their body can&rsquo;t handle resulting in heart failure, legs fracture, breathing disabilities, and skin problems.</p>\r\n\r\n	<p>Talking about the environment in which they are kept is heart shattering. In their natural habitat they are enjoying and joyful animals but place where they are kept is extremely poor bounding them in very less space as that place is fully stuffed of chicken exceeding the quantity it can contain. Coming to lights, they are kept under harsh artificial light in room packed with thousands of chickens and on the other part they also face darkness in sheds for more than five hours a day.</p>\r\n\r\n	<p>As a human if you visit the farm, you&rsquo;ll see the long carpet of white chicken stacked one over other with foul smell of ammonia that you can barely forget when you come back in fresh air.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"col-md-6 mt-3\"><b>MASSIVE SCALE</b>\r\n\r\n<p>If it is possible let&rsquo;s focus on life of just one chicken in a poultry farm. The congested are in which they live, the amount of sunlight they get, artificial lights, chemicals and other stuff they get injected. Now multiply this by one thousand, the number of chickens in that farm and multiply it further by thousand to get number of chickens in that region. This number keeps on rising further and from that we can realize how painful and suffering life these animals live. As a matter of fact, for every one human there are nine chickens that is totally outnumbering. Also it is unevenly distributed worldwide. In some countries annual consumption of chicken is 40 KG per person. That amounts about 15 chickens.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"col-md-6 mt-3\"><img alt=\"poultry\" src=\"https://karunaveg.com/uploaded_images/Poultry.jpeg\" style=\"width: 100%; height: 180px;\" /></div>\r\n<!-- --------------------------------------------------------------- -->\r\n\r\n<div class=\"col-md-12 mt-3\">\r\n<p><b>OPPORTUNITY AND TIME TO CHANGE</b></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Every problem has a perfect solution, so for this problem we can offer a solution to better the life of unlimited animals. Also, there&rsquo;s no need to get something new, solution is right in front of us, simply we can go vegan. We can eat farm grown fresh vegetables which equally fulfils our nutrition requirement. If you can&rsquo;t quit it quickly try eating healthier chicken and gradually, you&rsquo;ll feel better moving on to vegan meal entirely. This is a movement taking part worldwide and making a quick progress. Woken people from all demographics are coming forward saying that it&rsquo;s enough and over 500 companies are now working inn various field to make lives of chicken better.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n', 'Chickens, animals that face cruelty at a very mass rate on this planet. The amount of ', 'poultry', '2022-06-14 11:30:54', 11),
(8, 'Animal Cruelty ', '<div class=\"container\">\r\n    <div class=\"row\">\r\n    <div class=\"col-md-12 mt-3\">\r\n    <ul>\r\n        <li>\r\n        <p>Humans and animal have lived together on this planet happily for years. But in recent past animal cruelty is a harsh reality. At some points it&rsquo;s our carelessness at some point its unknowingly or at some point its intentional from our side. Talking about our homes, we keep pets love them treat them with care and enjoy with them but after some time we get bored and become ignorant, we delay their food, give them less time and sometimes beat them for minor mistakes. Another issue is that people keep pets more than their capacity, they keep too many pets and once they fail to handle them, they either abandon them or give them away to someone which cause pain of separation in animals. Animal looks good in their natural habitat living free enjoying with their groups but capturing them separating them from family at very young age killing them torturing them is not at all right.</p>\r\n        </li>\r\n    </ul>\r\n    </div>\r\n    \r\n    \r\n    <div class=\"col-md-6 mt-3\">\r\n    <ul>\r\n        <li><b>Let&rsquo;s have a look in what ways animals are abused and tortured </b></li><br>\r\n        <li>\r\n        <p><b>1. As For food: :</b> If we see around us a considerable amount of population is consuming meat products like chicken, pork, beef etc. but have we ever noticed that is that process in which they reach our home safe secure and clean. If we have a look at individual fields like poultry, chickens are kept in very unhygienic conditions and injected with chemicals to increase their weight. Talking about cattle&rsquo;s the space they take for animal farms and grazing lands is too much and can be used in other valuable businesses as well.</p>\r\n        </li>\r\n    </ul>\r\n    </div>\r\n    \r\n    <div class=\"col-md-6 mt-3\"><img alt=\"animal-cruelty\" src=\"https://karunaveg.com/uploaded_images/animal%20cruelty-ff.jpeg\" style=\"width: 100%; height: 180px;\" /></div>\r\n    \r\n    <div class=\"col-md-6 mt-3\"><img alt=\"animal-cruelty\" src=\"https://karunaveg.com/uploaded_images/Animal%20Cruelty.jpeg\" style=\"width: 100%; height: 180px;\" /></div>\r\n\r\n    <div class=\"col-md-6 mt-3\">\r\n    <ul>\r\n        <li>\r\n        <p><b>2. Fashion: :</b> We have seen this thing globally that people peel off tiger or lions&rsquo; skin, horn of rhinoceros or elephant and other animal part after illegally poaching them just to hang them on walls, making coats or using them as decorative items at home. These animals become victims of illegal killings and lose their life just for some people to get decorative items. As a result of all these activities these species are getting endangered and many species are already extinct from some parts of world. Beside these wild animal killings there are other animals like cows, buffalo, kangaroos, and lambs whose skin is used to make leather items like belts, shoes and other fashion products. These animals are killed on a massive scale for their skins. Moving on from clothing items there are animals like deer who are being poached for chemicals found in their body used to make perfumes.</p>\r\n        </li>\r\n    </ul>\r\n    </div>\r\n    \r\n    \r\n    <div class=\"col-md-6 mt-3\">\r\n    <ul>\r\n        <li>\r\n        <p><b>3. For entertainment:</b> Even as adults we are indulged in animal cruelty just for sake of entertainment or showing off. We&rsquo;ve recently came across many videos of people shooting dogs just to make videos or checking range of gun. Also, the tradition of animal fighting&rsquo;s is very much example of animal cruelty, it includes bull fighting, man vs tiger/ lion or any other animal fighting against each other just for sake of entertainment. Keeping animals in zoo trapped in limited region away from their natural habitat just for people to see them is also animal abuse, and many a times we notice people throwing stones and other things at those animals which is not a good thing.</p>\r\n        </li>\r\n    </ul>\r\n    </div>\r\n    <div class=\"col-md-6 mt-3\"><img alt=\"animal-cruelty\" src=\"https://karunaveg.com/uploaded_images/animal-cruelty-fe.jpeg\" style=\"width: 100%; height: 180px;\" /></div>\r\n\r\n    <!-- --------------------------------------------------------------- -->\r\n    \r\n    <div class=\"col-md-6 mt-3\"><img alt=\"animal-cruelty\" src=\"https://karunaveg.com/uploaded_images/Animal%20Cruelty%202.jpeg\" style=\"width: 100%; height: 180px;\" /></div>\r\n    \r\n    <div class=\"col-md-6 mt-3\">\r\n    <ul>\r\n        <li>\r\n        <p><b>4. Scientific experiment: </b> scientific experiments related to vaccines, medicines, chemical products for human etc. are firstly carried out on animal samples like hamster, dogs, rabbits and sheep. Many of these trials are carried out in a very inhuman way without proper testing that if they are capable of trials or not. And if the subject loses life in trial, they are dumbed without proper treatment which create a huge chance of disease getting spread in that region where they are dumped. Out of these medicine trials many dangerous trials are also conducted on animals like smoke of cigarettes are given to dogs and monkeys to inhale and check its effects. All these experiment of forced feeding, inhale of toxic fumes, pesticide testing and dripping chemicals into sensitive eyes of young animal subject are very inhuman and should be stopped.</p>\r\n        </li>\r\n    </ul>\r\n    </div>\r\n    <!-- --------------------------------------------------------------- -->\r\n    \r\n    <div class=\"col-md-6 mt-3\">\r\n    <ul>\r\n        <li>\r\n        <p><b>5. Rituals: </b> in this century we see a lot of rituals that include animal sacrifice. Like in many villages of India sheep, buffalos, goat and pigs are beheaded in the name of God. All these bloodsheds, sacrifices and loss of life for God is not at all right. Many people claim that no religion tells to make sacrifice, promote killing or sacrifice someone innocent but still such activities are carried out and no one is doing anything to stop such things.</p>\r\n        <b>Anthony D. Williams said- &ldquo;Be kind to every kind, not just mankind&rdquo;</b></li>\r\n    </ul>\r\n    </div>\r\n    \r\n    <div class=\"col-md-6 mt-3\"><img alt=\"animal-cruelty\" src=\"https://karunaveg.com/uploaded_images/Animal%20Cruelty3.jpeg\" style=\"width: 100%; height: 180px;\" /></div>\r\n    <!-- --------------------------------------------------------------- -->\r\n    \r\n    <div class=\"col-md-12 mt-3\">\r\n    <ul>\r\n        <li>\r\n        <p>So it is an opportunity for us to teach our next generation how to be kind and act like human being by treating every other living being with compassion and love. So we just need to remember that these animals also have family and they live happily, they don&rsquo;t even have anything to communicate and beg for mercy or complaint. Love them and they&rsquo;ll love you back.</p>\r\n        </li>\r\n    </ul>\r\n    </div>\r\n    </div>\r\n    </div>\r\n    ', 'Humans and animal have lived together on this planet happily for years. But in recent past animal', 'animal-cruelty', '2022-06-16 07:47:57', 3),
(10, 'Man vs Animal', '<div class=\"container\">\r\n<div class=\"row\">\r\n<div class=\"col-md-12 mt-3\">\r\n<ul>\r\n	\r\n	<p>Since ages animal and man have been living together. Animal were of multiple use to human beings they helped us in hunting, protected us and most importantly provided us company in tough times. Even today we have pets like dogs, cats, fishes which is a major source of positivity in our entire house. In return human also helped animal in various ways like we cared for them, feed them, provide them a safe shelter etc. We share unconditional bond with animals, they can easily sense our mood and have ability to fill our mind with joy and happiness that we can&rsquo;t get even from closest human relation. There is clear evidence to show us that human existence was majorly dependent on animals.</p>\r\n	\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"col-md-6 mt-3\">\r\n<ul>\r\n	\r\n	<p>Animals are important part of ecosystem; you can&rsquo;t imagine Coral Reef without fishes or a sky without birds. Each animal plays their specific role in maintaining ecosystem, if each animal has same role in ecosystem, it would be like all the farmers of world growing same product. Just like farming can&rsquo;t go on without diversity, same way ecosystem can go on without diversity in ecosystem. All ecosystem moves only if wildlife pushes them. Talking about science the energy released by primary source i.e., sun is stabilised by animals or else the energy would be accumulated and ecosystem would collapse. The basics of law of nature says that animal exist as they are most powerful living being to avoid environmental chaos.</p>\r\n	\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"col-md-6 mt-3\"><img alt=\"man-vs-animal\" src=\"https://karunaveg.com/uploaded_images/Man%20vs%20Animal1.jpeg\" style=\"width: 100%; height: 180px;\" /></div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"col-md-12 mt-3\">\r\n\r\n	<b>Best companions</b><br>\r\n	\r\n	<p>From stress reduction to increased healing and improved mood human and animal bond benefits us in multiple ways. We should make sure to provide them basic necessities like food and shelter and in return they make our life better. Let&rsquo;s study all these points in detail:</p>\r\n	\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"col-md-6 mt-3\"><img alt=\"man-vs-animal\" src=\"https://karunaveg.com/uploaded_images/man-vs-anim.jpeg\" style=\"width: 100%; height: 400px;\" /></div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"col-md-6 mt-3\">\r\n<ul>\r\n\r\n	<p><b>1. Reduce stress: </b> a pet owner helps you with regular exercise and low stress by regulating blood pressure. Having an animal company always turn out to be a good experience for human with reduced stress and better lifestyle.</p>\r\n	\r\n	\r\n	<p><b>2. Improved mood: </b>Studies show that spending time with your animal, playing with them or taking them for a walk are some of the basic tasks that releases chemical in your brain which are responsible for keeping you happy, providing mental support and recover from traumas.</p>\r\n	\r\n	\r\n	<p><b>3. Immunity improvement:</b> It is being noticed that those kids who are raised with animal are very less likely to get any sort of allergies from animal or environment. In addition, staying with animal reduces chance of getting asthma or any other breathing issues.</p>\r\n	\r\n	\r\n	<p><b>4. Social interaction:</b> Senior citizen or those people who barely get time to interact with their neighbours or friends have a great opportunity can interact with other while taking pet for a walk. This deeply improve your social activities in your daily lifecycle.</p>\r\n	\r\n	\r\n	<p><b>5. Emotional support: </b>Animals can easily sense your mood and stays with you even in hardest time despite of your financial condition or how you treat them. Your pet always provides you unconditional love and emotional support without any expectation or any demand.</p>\r\n	\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"col-md-12 mt-3\">\r\n<ul>\r\n	<b>Animal Welfare</b>\r\n	\r\n	<p>Animal farmers, scientists, trainers, breeders, zookeepers etc who work with animal related field are very close to animals and should take a special care of animals that their basic rights, needs and necessities are fulfilled. They should make sure availability of complete fresh diet, food/water, proper medical treatment, sanitization, handling them with care, their socialisation and a good environment to live in. Best practices should be there for animals to live a comfortable and happy life. Proper policies and principles of animal welfare should be followed.</p>\r\n	\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n\r\n<div class=\"col-md-6 mt-3\">\r\n<ul>\r\n	<b>One example of such policy is five freedoms. </b><br>\r\n\r\n	<p><b>1. Freedom from hunger and thirst:</b> Complete access to fresh food and water to stay healthy and fit.\r\n	\r\n	\r\n	<br><b>2. Freedom from discomfort: </b>A comfortable resting area and a good shelter should be provided to animals.\r\n	\r\n	\r\n	<br><b>3. Freedom from pain, disease or injury:</b> A quick and effective treatment should be given to animals if any incident happens.\r\n	\r\n	\r\n	<br><b>4. Freedom to express:</b> A proper space should be given to them to express themselves with facilities and company of same type.\r\n	\r\n	\r\n	<br><b>5. Freedom from fear: </b>No animal should have mental suffering of any kind.</p>\r\n	\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"col-md-6 mt-3\"><img alt=\"man-vs-animal\" src=\"https://karunaveg.com/uploaded_images/Man%20vs%20Animal3.jpeg\" style=\"width: 100%; height: 180px;\" /></div>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<div class=\"col-md-12 mt-3\">\r\n<ul>\r\n	<b>Animal Rights</b>\r\n	<p>Animal rights are moral principles based on the fact that all the animals deserve a life that they want to live without any boundations or any kind of desire from humans. Animal rights are same as human right with same motive, to make a better world and ensure there is no crime being committed but for non-humans. These rights are direct actions against any kind of brutality against animals be it for farm purpose, food, experiments or any other reason. Animal rights are violated even when it comes to destruction of animal habitat like forests or oceans. All these factors have a very bad effect on life of all animals.</p>\r\n	\r\n	\r\n	<b>Some examples of animal rights are:</b><br>\r\n	\r\n	<li>&bull; Animal might not be used for food </li>              \r\n	<li>&bull; Animal might  be hunted.</li>        \r\n	<li>&bull; Their habitat must be protected. </li>\r\n	<li>&bull; Animal might not be bred.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<!-- --------------------------------------------------------------- -->\r\n\r\n<div class=\"col-md-6 mt-3\">\r\n<ul>\r\n	\r\n	<p>If animal rights are important factor that can totally eliminate animal abuse worldwide and this would be a major for entire ecosystem and world by eliminating problems like water or air pollution, deforestation, global warming or greenhouse effect etc. So its quite clear that indeed animal rights are important and must be applied everywhere, as animals can&rsquo;t complaint or beg for mercy so we humans ourself have to see what&rsquo;s going around and how can we bring a change or else unwanted conditions will arise just like today where total farm animals outnumber the population of wild animals. A world where animals are free from exploitation of human being still seems quite far but many people/ groups are coming together to raise voice and aware people what these animals experience in such farms, factories and science labs. They have a hope that one day they will get a fair and loved treatment from human hands.</p>\r\n	\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"col-md-6 mt-3\"><img alt=\"man-vs-animal\" src=\"https://karunaveg.com/uploaded_images/Man%20vs%20Animal2.jpeg\" style=\"width: 100%; height: 180px;\" /></div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n', 'Since ages animal and man have been living together. Animal were of multiple use to human', 'man-vs-animal', '2022-06-26 15:32:33', 8);

