(4, '  GOD WAY OF WORSHIP ||', 'Some people say we cut  animals in one shot because animals will not feel any pain and some people say we cut animals slowly and steadily because animals will not feel any sadness or will not upset. Are such people are humans or what is there any sense in these line ? God will never say or order to do such activities. This is just Self Made Theories to give justification and satisfaction to themselves. People doing such activities like eating animals to worship god. Animals are the most beautiful creations made by God and you are killing them. How can you expect from God that he will listen to you or fulfill your needs. Hell (Ã Â¤Â¨Ã Â¤Â°Ã Â¤â€¢) is ready for such people by god. Animals want to be Respected and loved. So, respect them if you want to be respected by Animals. Question raise by some people then what we will eat ? Cook some Basmati rice with ghee , Roti , Dal and Halwa and Worship God with positive thoughts and Heart. This is the perfect way to Worship God. \r\nSTOP ANIMAL ABUSE AND STOP CUTTING THEM,\r\nRESPECT ANIMALS AND WORSHIP GOD,\r\nYOUR LIFE WILL BE FULL OF HAPPINESS AND JOY!\r\n\r\n<br> In the end Beautiful Lines by Kabir Sahab\r\n<br> Ã Â¤Â®Ã Â¤Â¾Ã Â¤Â¤Ã Â¤Â¾ Ã Â¤ÂªÃ Â¤Â¿Ã Â¤Â¤Ã Â¤Â¾ Ã Â¤Â®Ã Â¤Â¿Ã Â¤Â² Ã Â¤Å“Ã Â¤Â¾Ã Â¤ÂÃ Â¤â€šÃ Â¤â€”Ã Â¥â€¡, Ã Â¤Â²Ã Â¤Â¾Ã Â¤â€“ Ã Â¤Å¡Ã Â¥Å’Ã Â¤Â°Ã Â¤Â¾Ã Â¤Â¸Ã Â¥â‚¬ Ã Â¤Â®Ã Â¤Â¾Ã Â¤Â¹Ã Â¥â‚¬!\r\n<br> Ã Â¤Â¸Ã Â¤Â¤Ã Â¤â€”Ã Â¥ÂÃ Â¤Â°Ã Â¥Â Ã Â¤Â¸Ã Â¥â€¡Ã Â¤ÂµÃ Â¤Â¾ Ã Â¤â€Ã Â¤Â° Ã Â¤Â¬Ã Â¤â€šÃ Â¤Â¦Ã Â¤â€”Ã Â¥â‚¬ Ã Â¤Â­Ã Â¤Â¾Ã Â¤Ë† Ã Â¤Â«Ã Â¤Â¿Ã Â¤Â° Ã Â¤Â®Ã Â¤Â¿Ã Â¤Â²Ã Â¤Â¨ Ã Â¤Â¨Ã Â¤Â¹Ã Â¥â‚¬Ã Â¤â€š! \r\n<br> Ã Â¤Â¸Ã Â¤â€šÃ Â¤Â¤, Ã Â¤Â¸Ã Â¤Â®Ã Â¤Â¾Ã Â¤â€”Ã Â¤Â®, Ã Â¤Â¹Ã Â¤Â°Ã Â¤Â¿ Ã Â¤â€¢Ã Â¤Â¥Ã Â¤Â¾ Ã Â¤Â¤Ã Â¥ÂÃ Â¤Â²Ã Â¤Â¸Ã Â¥â‚¬ Ã Â¤Â¦Ã Â¥ÂÃ Â¤Â°Ã Â¥ÂÃ Â¤Â²Ã Â¤Â­ Ã Â¤Â¦Ã Â¥â€¹Ã Â¤Â¯! \r\n<br> Ã Â¤Â¸Ã Â¥ÂÃ Â¤Â¤ Ã Â¤Â§Ã Â¤Â¾Ã Â¤Â°Ã Â¤Â¾ Ã Â¤Â§Ã Â¤Â¨ Ã Â¤Â²Ã Â¤â€¢Ã Â¥ÂÃ Â¤Â·Ã Â¥ÂÃ Â¤Â®Ã Â¥â‚¬, Ã Â¤ËœÃ Â¤Â° Ã Â¤ÂªÃ Â¤Â¾Ã Â¤ÂªÃ Â¥â‚¬ Ã Â¤â€¢Ã Â¥â€¡ Ã Â¤Â­Ã Â¥â‚¬ Ã Â¤Â¹Ã Â¥â€¹Ã Â¤Â¯!', '', 'https://www.youtube.com/embed/bZiBNbpH0s4', 0, '2022-06-28 07:46:47'),
(5, 'Ã Â¤Â®Ã Â¤Â¾Ã Â¤Â¨Ã Â¤Âµ Ã Â¤Â¶Ã Â¤Â°Ã Â¥â‚¬Ã Â¤Â° Ã Â¤Â®Ã Â¥â€¡Ã Â¤â€š Ã Â¤Â®Ã Â¤Â¾Ã Â¤â€šÃ Â¤Â¸Ã Â¤Â¾Ã Â¤Â¹Ã Â¤Â¾Ã Â¤Â° Ã Â¤â€¢Ã Â¤Â°Ã Â¤Â¨Ã Â¥â€¡ Ã Â¤Â¸Ã Â¥â€¡ Ã Â¤â€¢Ã Â¥ÂÃ Â¤Â¯Ã Â¤Â¾ Ã Â¤Â¹Ã Â¥â€¹Ã Â¤Â¤Ã Â¤Â¾ Ã Â¤Â¹Ã Â¥Ë† ?', '\"PEACE STARTS ON OUR PLATE\"\r\nOnce upon a time, Mother asked her son to \"leave Non-Veg food for life\". When they went to Haridwar for 10 days he swear that he will not eat Non-Veg again but after returning back home on the 11th day he cooked an egg in the house. His mom asked \"why do you start non veg again \"he said, \"I left nonveg for Ganga, not for home and we are in our house so I started again\". So if he cant leave Nonveg, he has 100 excuses to give, so cant Leave non-veg. Some people don\'t eat non veg when  they keep fast for their Gods and Goddess but in the end, after that, they went to eat nonveg, is it worth worshiping like these? There is a difference between Vegan and \r\nNon-Veg animals like Lion and cheetahs also eat other animals but at the same time cow, and zebra only eat fruits and grass and we truly worship cows. So when you adopt nonveg food, your rebirth will be in the animal race(Ã Â¤ÂªÃ Â¤Â¶Ã Â¥Â Ã Â¤Å“Ã Â¤Â¾Ã Â¤Â¤Ã Â¥â‚¬). So Adopt Veg Food for life. \r\n<br>\r\n<br> In the end, we want to share a beautiful quote \r\n<br> \"If you think that being vegan is hard, imagine being a factory-farmed animal\".', '', 'https://www.youtube.com/embed/MhrLhDsg9TI', 1, '2022-06-29 18:55:51'),
(7, 'Reason for Cancer', 'In today\'s generation Cancer is spreading like a virus. But do you know why it is spreading so fastly? In all age groups, everyone is suffering from cancer. According to Survey, life expectancy is to be not more than the Age of 70 to 80 in cities and states. In every home, someone is suffering from diseases like Blood pressure, Diabities, Heart Problems, Cancer, etc. We don\'t like to say these things but it\'s true. Everyone deserves a happy life. There\'s a reason all behind this and that reason is Chemicals used in food. Various kinds of chemicals using in all food. Companies use harmful preservatives and chemicals in all types of food products whether it is lays , maggie , chips , cold drinks , jam, wheat, moong and even Bajra etc. All farmers use chemicals for growing crops in quantity and decreasing quality. There\'s hardly left any organic food that\'s why Organic products is more expensive than Normal food products. \r\nEveryone\'s body\'s resistance is different some people who have a strong immune system can recover from these problems but on the other hand, some people who had a weak immune system can hardly recover. There\'s no limit to consuming junk food and packed drinks. So companies use harmful colors, sodium nitrate, high Frutos, poor quality corn syrup, and oil to make these products delicious and fresh. We consume these products for a long time that\'s why the body\'s resistance becomes low. I will give you an example in old times farmers use 1 Quilton of wheat seeds and it produces 3 to 5 max Quilton of wheat. It Quality is full of nutrients and protein. But today period of time they use various kinds of chemicals and pesticides that if we use 1 Quilton of wheat, it produces 25 to 30 Quilton of wheat like 10 times from before so it decreases the quality and people suffer. Choose your food products wisely and eat healthy, avoid packed drinks and junk food and make your immune system strong. Stay Healthy and Stay Safe! Use organic products as much as you can!', '', 'https://www.youtube.com/embed/JDmgEmbxTss', 0, '2022-07-01 11:30:38'),
(9, 'Animal Experimentation', 'The use of non-human animals in studies that aim to regulate the factors that influence the behaviour or biological system under study is known as animal testing, also known as animal experimentation, animal research, and in vivo testing. Are we doing right experimentation ? We know animals and humans are not same but why cant be this experimentation be done humans because they feel pain , they suffer and can tell you about pain. What about animals ?\r\nWe do testing on animals just because we cant understand their language and actions. Its very bad for animals because the bleeding , fear producing , cage circling , screaming hurt that we shudder to even imagine. These all thing on the name of research and testing. They also feel loneliness , sadness , and pain just like as we do. It hurts. They also want to live just like as we do. We are all the same when it comes to pain, starvation, dehydration, and not wanting to pass away. Testing on animals give faulty results. Its wrong when we do it to animals because we cant explain to them. After the end testing you know what happens so its all unscientific. \r\n<br>\r\n<br> In the End We know ,\r\n<br> IN SILENCE THEY SUFFER,\r\n<br> IN LONELINESS THEY DIE! \r\n<br> STOP ANIMAL EXPERIMENTATION,\r\nCOZ\' ALL LIFE MATTERS,\r\nWANT TO LIVE TOGETHER IN THE SAME NATION!', '', 'https://www.youtube.com/embed/bCAym1O23H8', 0, '2022-07-08 11:32:46'),
(10, '15 Harmful Chemicals Used in Daily Care Products', 'Do you know that 60% of skin care products are absorbed by your skin. European Union has banned more than 1300 Chemicals that can cause your skin. Today we are talking about 15 harmful chemicals. \r\n\r\n1. Parabens - It is used for Skincare and Makeup. It can also cause Brist cancer. Another problem used by this chemical is reproductive brain function.\r\n2. Phtalets - It is used in Hair Spray, shampoo, and nail polish. It can cause diseases such as Thyroid, Diabetes, and Infertility. \r\n3. Synthetic Colors- It is made of petroleum and Coal tar products. It is used in lipstick and Eyeshadow. Other problems caused by this chemical is Cancer, Skin irritation, and Acne breakouts. \r\n4. Fragrance - It is used to hide stinky smells. It is mainly used in Perfumes. Some problems caused by this are Allergies, Infertility, Diabetes, Thyroid etc. \r\n5. Triclosan - It is used as an anti-bacterial in toothpaste. There are chances that it can cause a Tumor.\r\n6. Toluen - It is a petrochemical solvent which is used in Nail polish, Hair dye. It is dangerous for children. It is known for Blood cancer and makes your immune system weak.\r\n7. Talc - It is used in Powder form, perfumes, Eyeshadow, and blush. There are chances it can cause you ovarian cancer. \r\n8. Oxybenzone - It is to be found in your lip balm, lip shade, and sunscreen the two other chemicals that can be found are an Octinoxate, Octocrylene which can harm your skin.\r\n9. Polyethylene Glycol( PEG ) - It is used in body lotions and sunscreen. If you use it for a long time there might be chances that it can cause you cancer. \r\n10. Formaldehyde - It is used in skin care products such as nail polish, hair gel, face masks, and hair spray as preservatives for stopping the growth of bacteria. It is known for asthma, neurotoxicity, scalp burns, and hair loss. \r\n11. Diethanolamine - It is a known cancer-causing agent. It is to be found in Body wash, soaps etc. It is also known for respiratory toxins. \r\n12. Ethylenediaminetetraacetic acid - It is to be found in toothpaste and is known for toxicity. \r\n13. Mineral Oil - It is found to be in hair oil and lotion. Other harmful substances is also used such as TPHQ, BPT, Artificial Fragrance and various kind of harmful chemicals is also present. \r\n14. Polyethylene Glycol(PEGs) - It is used in body lotions, and sunscreen. It can damage your skin.\r\n15. Sodium Lauryl Sulfate - It is used in hand wash, body washing, and shampoo. It can also lead to cancer. \r\n<br>\r\n<br> In the end,\r\n<br> PLEASE TAKE THESE CHEMICALS SERIOUS AND CHOOSE YOUR DAILY SKIN CARE PRODUCTS!\r\n<br> For More Details, Please see the video and Spread Awareness!\r\n', '', 'https://www.youtube.com/embed/FtiDbSLNlu0', 5, '2022-07-12 18:56:12'),
(11, 'GO VEGAN', 'Veganism is the practice of declininig from the use of animal products, particularly in diet, and an research and practice that rejects the commodity status of animals. Dietary vegans, also known as \"strict vegetarians\", refuse from consuming meat, eggs, and any other animal-derived substances. An ethical vegan is someone who not only follows a plant-based diet but also extends the rules into other areas of their lives. They opposes the use of animals for any purpose and tries to avoid any cruelty and exploitation of all animals including humans.Another term is \"environmental veganism\", which refers to the avoidance of animal products in the  industrial farming of animals which  damaging environmental and unsustainable.On the other hand opposite of veganism is speciesism which is meant to thought as a practice  thinking that humans are better than animals . It is also treating animals worse than humans. For example, humans often kill animals to eat. Human cannibalism is the act or practice of humans eating the flesh or internal organs of other human beings. \'Speciesism\' is the idea that being human is a good enough reason for human animals to have greater moral rights than non-human animals, it is a bias in favour of the interests of members of one\'s own species and against those of members of other species.\r\n\'Speciesism\' is the idea that being human is a good enough reason for human animals to have greater moral rights than non-human animals, a prejudice or bias in favour of the interests of members of one\'s own species and against those of members of other species.\r\nIt teaches us we humans thought that we are superior over some animals so that we have some rights to slave animals for our benefit.. \r\nWe think their lives of some animals are more valuable than the lives of other as we pet dog, cat, parrot, but they are insane for other. \r\nIt\'s time to recognize that all living beings deserve to be treated with respect and compassion. We can reject speciesism and act with integrity and consistency toward all living beings, and the first step is to recognize that every animal has the right to live free from human exploitation.\r\nVegans are at reduced risk of certain health conditions, including ischemic heart disease, type 2 diabetes, hypertension, certain types of cancer, and obesity. \r\n<br>\r\n<br> In the end, our main Agenda is to Encourage people to become Vegan, or at the very least, Vegetarian.', '', 'https://www.youtube.com/embed/hiJKbXZrgts', 0, '2022-07-17 12:38:28'),
(12, 'Veg Vs Non Veg', 'The WHO report non-veggie lover nourishment causes 159 distinct sorts of infections. The most well-known illnesses caused because of it are heart ailments, hypertension, kidney issue, bother bladder issues, wounds in supply routes, dermatitis, loss of motion, tuberculosis, stoppage, torments, joint inflammation, craziness and so on.\r\nAt the point when 8 kg of vegetable protein is sustained to the creatures, they deliver one kg of meat protein. so being vegetarian not save our life but also innocent  as the eggs are filled with toxic and hurtful components. An egg is a reason for a few genuine infections; the elevated cholesterol content builds the danger of coronary illness. If we talk about eggs the Hens eat sputum, mucus, nose discharges, worms, germs, and other such squalid things. The eggs are created from these things.  The irresistible microorganisms entering the egg through these pores Ã¢â‚¬â€œ salmonella, shigella, and Staphylococci.Bile and pancreatic juices of the egg are ineffectual on egg white.\r\nIn meat, the cholesterol present may result in accumulation of fats (cholesterol) in the veins and arteries which will cause obstruction in the blood vessels which may result in major health related problems like chronic obstructive pulmonary disease (COPD), hypertension (increased blood pressure), cardiac arrest, atherosclerosis etc.t is strongly believed that the SARS-CoV-2 virus responsible for causing this deadly pandemic has originated from a wet market in Wuhan, China, many strict non-vegetarians too turned to be strict vegetarians in the last couple of months in risk of corona virus.So for the healthy lifestyle we should follow healthy and balanced diet including a rich array of fruits and vegetables, staying physically active.', '', 'https://www.youtube.com/embed/6Objyv1vI2g', 0, '2022-07-22 08:33:18'),
(13, 'What If Everyone Becomes Vegetarian In this World!', 'They started by looking at climate change. One-quarter to one-third of all co2 emissions globally are attributed to the production of food, with the cattle sector bearing the lion\'s share of the blame. Despite this, the impact of our eating habits on climate change is frequently overlooked. For instance, a typical family of four in the US produces more greenhouse gases due to their consumption of meat, which is frequently brought up in conversations about global warming.\r\nTim Benton, a food security specialist at the University of Leeds, claims that \"the majority of people don\'t think of the significance of food on climate change.\" But even a little reduction in meat consumption might significantly improve conditions for our children and grandchildren.\r\n<br>\r\nWhat would occur if by 2050 everyone adopted a vegetarian diet?. According to the findings, food-related emissions would decrease by around 60% as a result of eliminating red meat. Instead, if everyone became vegan, emissions would fall by about 70%.\r\n\"We found that you could only stabilise the ratio of food-related emissions to all emissions if everyone adopted a plant-based diet,\" Springmann adds. \"When looking at what would be in accordance with avoiding hazardous levels of climate change.\" \"That scenario is not very likely, but it emphasises the significance of emissions related to food in the future.\"\r\nFood, especially cattle, takes up a lot of space and is a source of biodiversity loss, greenhouse gas emissions, and land conversion. Around five billion hectares (12 billion acres) of agricultural land are used for cattle worldwide.\r\nIf everyone became a vegetarian, we should ideally devote at least 80% of that pastureland to the restoration of grasslands and woodlands, which would help slow down climate change by capturing carbon. Former pastures might be turned into natural habitats, which would certainly benefit biodiversity as well as huge herbivores like buffalo that were driven out by cattle and predators like wolves that are sometimes killed in reprisal for attacking livestock.\r\n<br>\r\nTo make up for any gaps in the food supply, the remaining 10 to 20 percent of the previous pastureland may be used to grow more crops. Because one-third of the area currently utilised for crops is devoted to providing food for livestockÃ¢â‚¬â€rather than for humansÃ¢â‚¬â€rather than for humans, this relatively little increase in agricultural land would more than make up for the loss of meat.\r\n<br>\r\nIf everyone becomes vegetarian by 2050, coronary heart disease, diabetes, stroke, and several malignancies would decline, resulting in a 6Ã¢â‚¬â€œ10% decrease in global mortality. Half of that drop is attributable to eliminating red meat, with the remaining advantages coming from reducing calorie intake and boosting fruit and vegetable consumption. These advantages would be amplified further by a global vegan diet: while vegetarianism would prevent roughly 7 million deaths annually, veganism would prevent up to 8 million. A reduction in the number of persons with chronic food-related disorders would also result in lower medical costs, saving around 2% to 3% of the world\'s GDP.\r\n<br>\r\nIn the end Veganism has more benefits than Non Veg for your Health and as well as for our Global Warming', '', 'https://www.youtube.com/embed/nfCdgOfJ2oE', 0, '2022-08-04 08:35:47'),
(14, 'Healthy Food is Equal to Healthy Life', 'A healthy diet includes the following:\r\nFruit, vegetables, legumes, nuts, and whole grains, such as lentils and beans (e.g. unprocessed maize, millet, oats, wheat and brown rice).\r\na minimum of 400 g (five pieces), or five portions, of fruit and vegetables per day, omitting starchy roots like potatoes, sweet potatoes, and cassava.\r\nLess than 10% of total energy intake from free sugars, which is equal to 50 g (or around 12 level teaspoons) for a person of healthy body weight consuming about 2000 calories per day, is recommended for additional health benefits. However, less than 5% of total energy intake is preferable. All added sugars to food or beverages, whether by the producer, cook, or consumer, as well as sugars found naturally in honey, syrups, fruit juices, and fruit juice concentrates, are considered free sugars.\r\n30 percent or less of total energy intake from fats . Saturated fats, which are present in fatty meat, butter, palm and coconut oil, cream, cheese, ghee, and lard, as well as trans-fats of all kinds, including ruminant trans-fats, are to be avoided. These fats can also be found in baked and fried foods, as well as in pre-packaged snacks and foods like frozen pizza, pies, cookies, biscuits, wafers, and cooking oils and spreads (found in meat and dairy foods from ruminant animals, such as cows, sheep, goats and camels). Saturated fat intake should be kept to less than 10% of total energy intake, and trans fat intake should be kept to less than 1% of total calorie intake, according to recommendations. Trans-fats manufactured industrially, in particular, do not belong in a healthy diet and should be avoided .\r\nLess than 5  g of salt (equivalent to about one teaspoon) per day.  Salt should be iodized.\r\n<br>\r\nVeggies and fruits\r\nIn addition to lowering the risk of NCDs, eating at least 400 g, or five pieces, of fruit and vegetables each day helps to ensure that one gets enough dietary fibre each day.\r\nBy constantly adding vegetables in meals, snacking on fresh fruit and raw vegetables, eating fruit and vegetables that are in season, and eating a variety of fruits and vegetables, one can increase their intake of fruits and vegetables.\r\n<br>\r\nThe Second International Conference on Nutrition was convened by WHO and the Food and Agriculture Organization of the United Nations (FAO) in November 2014. (ICN2). ICN2 approved the Framework for Action (18) and the Rome Declaration on Nutrition (17), which suggest a number of policy alternatives and measures to support varied, secure, and healthy meals at all stages of life. WHO is assisting nations in carrying out the agreements established at ICN2.\r\n<br>\r\nÃ Â¤Â®Ã Â¤Â¨Ã Â¥ÂÃ Â¤Â·Ã Â¥ÂÃ Â¤Â¯Ã Â¥â€¹Ã Â¤â€š Ã Â¤â€¢Ã Â¥â€¡ Ã Â¤Â²Ã Â¤Â¿Ã Â¤Â 3 Ã Â¤â€ Ã Â¤Å¡Ã Â¤Â°Ã Â¤Â£\r\n1. Ã Â¤Â¸Ã Â¤Â¾Ã Â¤Â¤Ã Â¥ÂÃ Â¤ÂµÃ Â¤Â¿Ã Â¤â€¢-Ã Â¤Â­Ã Â¤â€¢Ã Â¥ÂÃ Â¤Â¤Ã Â¤Â¿, Ã Â¤â€¦Ã Â¤Â¨Ã Â¥ÂÃ Â¤Â·Ã Â¤Â¾Ã Â¤Â¸Ã Â¤Â¨ Ã Â¤â€¢Ã Â¤Â¾ Ã Â¤Â­Ã Â¤Â¾Ã Â¤ÂµÃ Â¥Â¤\r\n2. Ã Â¤Â¤Ã Â¤Â¾Ã Â¤Â®Ã Â¤Â¸Ã Â¤Â¿Ã Â¤â€¢- Ã Â¤â€¢Ã Â¥ÂÃ Â¤Â¨Ã Â¥ÂÃ Â¤Â¥Ã Â¤Â¾, Ã Â¤â€¡Ã Â¤Â¶Ã Â¥ÂÃ Â¤Â¯ Ã Â¤â€¢Ã Â¤Â¾ Ã Â¤ÂªÃ Â¥ÂÃ Â¤Â°Ã Â¤Â­Ã Â¤Â¾Ã Â¤ÂµÃ Â¥Â¤\r\n3. Ã Â¤Â°Ã Â¤Â¾Ã Â¤Å“Ã Â¤Â¸Ã Â¤Â¿Ã Â¤â€¢Ã Â¤Â¾ - Ã Â¤Â®Ã Â¤Â¾Ã Â¤Â¥Ã Â¥â€¡ Ã Â¤ÂªÃ Â¤Â° Ã Â¤Â²Ã Â¤Â¾Ã Â¤Â²Ã Â¤Â¸Ã Â¤Â¾ Ã Â¤â€¦Ã Â¤Â¤Ã Â¤Â¿ Ã Â¤â€°Ã Â¤Â¤Ã Â¥ÂÃ Â¤Â¸Ã Â¤Â¾Ã Â¤Â¹ Ã Â¤â€¢Ã Â¤Â¾ Ã Â¤ÂªÃ Â¥ÂÃ Â¤Â°Ã Â¤Â­Ã Â¤Â¾Ã Â¤ÂµÃ Â¥Â¤\r\n<br>\r\nNon Veg products will make you sick so products like Water, fruits, Milk, Curd, will make you more proteins and Nutrients.', '', 'https://www.youtube.com/embed/aqdyiIKOHUc', 0, '2022-08-08 08:37:45'),
